<br>
A really good shield can help catch up some on the tanking difference between a warrior and a paladin.  It'll also let you bash / stun.<br>
<br>
If I were a warrior, I'd probably dual wield, just to further help keep aggro on me.<br>
<br>
- Syll <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/bfirionavie.showUserPublicProfile?gid=dididaryth>Didi D Aryth</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Worshipping Tallonar since 3160</span><br>  Posts: 70<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(11/7/02 8:44 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm43.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=159.topic&index=2>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://users.bigpond.net.au/stbt/didi/a_didisig.gif height=120 width=120></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: 2HS or 1HS and Sheld</span><hr size=1> There was some debate of this already in this thread:<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE AUTOLINK START--><a href="http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm43.showMessage?topicID=148.topic">pub94.ezboard.com/ffirion...=148.topic</a><!--EZCODE AUTOLINK END--><br>
<br>
Basically, bash can be useful even for warriors at times - in particular, to interrupt spells, and to stun a running foe.  For a shadow knight (or paladin) who can't dual wield, it's particularly useful for interrupting spells.  I use my high damage 2-handed weapon for fighting non-casters, and always switch to a one-hander and shield when I'm up against a caster.<br>
<br>
Also you only listed 1HS and 2HS.  Paladins, like Knights and Warriors, should master all the forms of weaponry.  OK I've been shirking a wee bit on my 2HB but you definitely need 1HB and Piercing as well.   I believe Shintou has even trained hand to hand.  And there are 2HB weapons that will make it worth my while to keep working on that one also. <p><!--EZCODE CENTER START--><div style="text-align:center"><br>
