<br>
Basically, you need both for different situations.<br>
<br>
When you need to dish out the most possible damage, two handers for a knight all the way.  They simply do more damage.  Also, when damage shields are an issue.  When you need to interupt, one handers work better since they're faster and you can bash.  <br>
<br>
So yeah, both.<br>
<br>
