<br>
if you're hitting for near max damage and have a better ratio 1 hander then go one hander<br>
<br>
if you're hitting for marginal damage the 2handers larger damage bonus may pick up the slack ( and i've read that top end luclin mobs with crazy AC this is the way to go as well )<br>
<br>
if you're dueling another melee, *cough* 2 handed is the way to go. because even a generic warrior assuming they are moderately geared is going to put up ring 8 ds, chardok ring DS and potion DS. you can't afford to take that much damage chewing though a 5k tank ( this is somewhat relative to level but i know Reg is at least 60 so if he was dueling he'd be faceing this type of gear )<br>
<br>
also don't plate hydrids get a 2hs .. bash AA ?<br>
<br>
warriors tend to run dual weild to try to keep agro but any of the hybrids don't need weapon speed to do that any way.<br>
<br>
my solution : parse what you have, take a look at your class specific boards<br>
<br>
oh and for soloing i think 2hs is more effective just because you eat less repost damage <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/bfirionavie.showUserPublicProfile?gid=sevlin>Sevlin</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 21<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(11/8/02 5:02 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm43.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=159.topic&index=7>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: 2HS or 1HS and Sheld</span><hr size=1> In my experience, I tend to do more damage with a 1H and Shield than 2H, but it may likely be perception.  I've used a 12/23 Goranga Spiked Club for the past 15 or so levels, and even up against an Abram's Axe of the Stoic (30/48 with 14 damage bonus), I think I do more damage with the Club and Shield overall.  Sure, in some fights with the 2Her, I'll get a string of 80-120 damage hits that probably put my damage better than the Club, but if I parsed logs with both, I'd imagine the Club/Shield outdamages the axe more consistently.  However, this is with 120 STR, which likely keeps 2Hing from hitting the 90+ range more often.<br>
<br>
Another thing that I've noticed when soloing is that 2Hing can just really hurt sometimes.  Without a haste item, a 48 delay weapon is brutal if you miss once or twice.  The added AC (and in my case 50 HP) from a shield makes the fight a bit easier on the HP, too. <p> <!--EZCODE IMAGE START--><img src="http://www.members.shaw.ca/vae/sigv2-5.jpg"/><!--EZCODE IMAGE END--><br>
