At high lvl : 50+<br>
- big race : 2H all the way, like they have slam to interrupt<br>
- non big race : 2h will do more damage but you'd prefer to take 1+sheild against caster (especilly cleric CH or gaters)<br>
- 2H bahs AA : well bye bye 1H+shield ... 2h is the way and you can nowinterrupt as you have a shield.<br>
<br>
For the dmg output look at your weapon, in the hight end lvl, 2H do far more dmg than a 1H+shield.<br>
ex: a 45dmg/44dly 2H wepaon (dmg bonus of 47) do much more dmg then a 24dmg/22dly (dmg bonus 11) + shield at lvl 60.<br>
<br>
In the middle lvl (30 to 49), 1H or 2h will mostly depnd of your gear. <br>
<br>
On the last subject : diff with melee and non melee bonus. with a non melee yu only have the dly bonus of a weapon.<br>
A melee have dmg bonus that are scale to their lvl.<br>
Basicly a 60 war/sk/pal/rng will do no less than 11dmg per hit with his prim 1H, and 17+ (dly bonus) with a 2H.<br>
<br>
