<br>
For awhile my best weapon was a slow as mollases 2h piercing.<br>
<br>
But I put it away every time I went on a plannar raid... <br>
because resisting AoE damage and magic is the name of the game on allot of raids.  The resists I get from my crested mistmoore shield are too valuable to sacrifice.<br>
<br>
If your fighting say... Vox, and you get feared over and over while being killed by AoE damage, having a much higher damage 2 hander does nothing because you may barely ever get to use it.<br>
<br>
This is true of Vox and Nagaven, most all Kunark dragons, lots of Boss mobs also have various AoE effects.  In all of those cases... I am not the main tank.  So staying alive to do damage over time, rather than max damage to 1 or 2 sec.  is far more important.<br>
<br>
Also, in the off situation where I do get to be MT, damage output is not what MT is about.  It is preventing damage, absorbing damage, and maintaining agro so that the assistant tanks etc. land as much damage as possible.  As MT you get stunned more than anyone else.  You don't do any damage being stunned, but your ac still counts though, and bash helps you keep agro and reduce the damage done to you.<br>
<br>
Conversely, when ever I’m in a small group with no debuffer and we run into a mob with a DS… I wince for the poor monk or ranger standing next to me just soaking it up while I pull out ol’ slowbee bigwhollop and feel minimal effect from the Damage Shield. <br>
<br>
They both have their place.  At level 51 I had all my weapon skills maxed.  Now that I am 52, I am maxing them all again.<br>
<br>
