<br>
If you are the tank your job is to control aggro.  If you can do that with one 1H then put a shield in the other hand and save your cleric mana.  Tanks are not damage dealers - monks, rogues, wizzies etc. serve that role if the MT is doing his job.<br>
<br>
So I use a shield when:<br>
<br>
1.  I can control aggro with a shield and weapon.  I do less damage, but use less mana for heals.  Let my team do the damage.<br>
<br>
2.  Multiple mobs wailing on me.  In this case the beneifts of shield multiply its AC benefit with each extra mob.  The opposite is true if that hand is occupied by a weapon.  Again, save your cleric mana.<br>
